    "The target image's stain color foundation is mixed with the density maps to change only the colors while maintaining the intensity of the structures.",
    "The target image was chosen rather arbitrarily to encompass a wide range of colors from the dataset.",
    "Each image is normalized independently since removing the white pixels of the backdrop first is recommended because they are simply formed of the two base stain colors.",
    "One popular method for getting around the restrictions of applying neural networks to analyze huge images is to use small patches.",
    "Choosing the right patch size is essential to balance the analysis's resolution and processing needs."
